definitions.definition: Of, concerning , or in accordance with recorded history , ( particularly ) as opposed to legends , myths , and fictions .
examples: July 4, 1776, is a historic date. A great deal of historical research has been done on the events leading up to that day.
The historical works of Lord Macaulay and Edward Gibbon are in and of themselves historic.

subdefinitions.definition: About history ; depicting persons or events from history .

definitions.definition: Of, concerning , or in accordance with the past generally .

subdefinitions.definition: Former , erstwhile ; ( religious , obsolete ) lapsed , nominal .
One of various tenses or moods used to tell about past events, historic (tense).

definitions.definition: Of, concerning , or in accordance with the scholarly discipline of history .
examples: The State Historical Society of Wisconsin

subdefinitions.definition: Done in the manner of a historian : written as a development over time or in accordance with the historical method .
Synonym of historic : important or likely to be important to history and historians .
